---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Seeds - Dev Wells">
  <div class="min-h-screen px-phi-4 py-phi-6 max-w-[65ch] mx-auto">
    <main>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-light tracking-tight mb-phi-4">Seeds</h1>
      <p
        class="text-bark-600 dark:text-bark-400 italic mb-phi-5 text-lg leading-relaxed"
      >
        Raw ideas, snippets, and thoughts in their earliest form. Some may grow,
        others may not.
      </p>

      <div
        class="text-bark-400 dark:text-bark-600 text-center my-phi-5 font-mono"
      >
        ━━━ ◈ ━━━
      </div>

      <div class="grid gap-phi-4">
        <!-- Seed cards -->
        <div
          class="group bg-paper dark:bg-paper-dark border border-bark-200 dark:border-bark-800 border-l-4 border-l-sage-500 dark:border-l-sage-400 rounded-sm p-phi-4 hover:shadow-md hover:translate-x-1 transition-all duration-200 cursor-pointer"
        >
          <h3
            class="text-sage-700 dark:text-sage-400 font-mono text-sm mb-phi-2 flex items-center gap-2"
          >
            <span class="text-lg group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform"
              >💭</span
            > Thought
          </h3>
          <p class="text-ink dark:text-ink-dark leading-relaxed">
            What if we treated our codebases like gardens instead of factories?
            Pruning old growth, composting dead code, letting good patterns
            propagate naturally.
          </p>
          <time class="text-xs text-bark-500 dark:text-bark-400 mt-phi-2 block">
            Just now
          </time>
        </div>

        <div
          class="group bg-paper dark:bg-paper-dark border border-bark-200 dark:border-bark-800 border-l-4 border-l-flower-500 dark:border-l-flower-400 rounded-sm p-phi-4 hover:shadow-md hover:translate-x-1 transition-all duration-200 cursor-pointer"
        >
          <h3
            class="text-flower-700 dark:text-flower-400 font-mono text-sm mb-phi-2 flex items-center gap-2"
          >
            <span class="text-lg group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform"
              >🔧</span
            > Tool Idea
          </h3>
          <p class="text-ink dark:text-ink-dark leading-relaxed">
            A CLI that analyzes your git history and suggests which files might
            benefit from refactoring based on change frequency and size growth
            patterns.
          </p>
          <time class="text-xs text-bark-500 dark:text-bark-400 mt-phi-2 block">
            2 days ago
          </time>
        </div>

        <div
          class="group bg-paper dark:bg-paper-dark border border-bark-200 dark:border-bark-800 border-l-4 border-l-bark-500 dark:border-l-bark-400 rounded-sm p-phi-4 hover:shadow-md hover:translate-x-1 transition-all duration-200 cursor-pointer"
        >
          <h3
            class="text-bark-700 dark:text-bark-400 font-mono text-sm mb-phi-2 flex items-center gap-2"
          >
            <span class="text-lg group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform"
              >📝</span
            > Quote
          </h3>
          <blockquote
            class="text-ink dark:text-ink-dark leading-relaxed italic"
          >
            "The amateur software engineer worries about code. The professional
            worries about data structures and their relationships."
          </blockquote>
          <cite class="text-xs text-bark-500 dark:text-bark-400 mt-phi-2 block">
            — Rob Pike (attributed)
          </cite>
        </div>

        <div
          class="group bg-paper dark:bg-paper-dark border border-bark-200 dark:border-bark-800 border-l-4 border-l-sage-500 dark:border-l-sage-400 rounded-sm p-phi-4 hover:shadow-md hover:translate-x-1 transition-all duration-200 cursor-pointer"
        >
          <h3
            class="text-sage-700 dark:text-sage-400 font-mono text-sm mb-phi-2 flex items-center gap-2"
          >
            <span class="text-lg group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform"
              >🌱</span
            > Experiment
          </h3>
          <p class="text-ink dark:text-ink-dark leading-relaxed">
            Building this site with golden ratio spacing everywhere. So far the
            1.618 scale feels surprisingly natural for both typography and
            layout rhythm.
          </p>
          <time class="text-xs text-bark-500 dark:text-bark-400 mt-phi-2 block">
            1 week ago
          </time>
        </div>

        <div
          class="group bg-paper dark:bg-paper-dark border border-bark-200 dark:border-bark-800 border-l-4 border-l-flower-500 dark:border-l-flower-400 rounded-sm p-phi-4 hover:shadow-md hover:translate-x-1 transition-all duration-200 cursor-pointer"
        >
          <h3
            class="text-flower-700 dark:text-flower-400 font-mono text-sm mb-phi-2 flex items-center gap-2"
          >
            <span class="text-lg group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform"
              >🤔</span
            > Question
          </h3>
          <p class="text-ink dark:text-ink-dark leading-relaxed">
            Why do we call it "technical debt" when it's really more like
            "technical entropy"? Debt implies intention to repay. Entropy
            just... happens.
          </p>
          <time class="text-xs text-bark-500 dark:text-bark-400 mt-phi-2 block">
            2 weeks ago
          </time>
        </div>
      </div>

      <footer
        class="mt-phi-8 pt-phi-6 border-t border-sage-200 dark:border-sage-800"
      >
        <p class="text-sm text-bark-500 dark:text-bark-400 text-center italic">
          Not all seeds become trees, but all trees were once seeds.
        </p>
      </footer>
    </main>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .grid > div {
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .grid > div::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    width: 4px;
    height: 100%;
    background: inherit;
    transform: scaleY(0);
    transform-origin: top;
    transition: transform 0.3s ease;
  }

  .grid > div:hover::before {
    transform: scaleY(1);
  }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .grid > div {
      transition: none !important;
    }
    .grid > div span {
      transition: none !important;
    }
  }
</style>
